sentences.chinese: 希望大家諒解一下，嘿嘿。

sentences.english: He touched them on the head and went on working.

sentences.chinese: 嘿嘿，我可要好好睡上一頓了。

sentences.english: But I know that the girls definitely love smug myself, hey, me too.

definition: to laugh heartily/to burst into loud laughter
interjection indicating approval, appreciation or agreement
(literary) youngster/(old) young fellow (term of address used by the older generation)/(old) I, me (used in speaking to one's elders)
to give a hollow laugh/to force a smile/forced laugh/CL:聲|声[sheng1]
(affectionate form of address for a male who is not very much younger than oneself) my boy/old pal
